    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to third millennium Chalcolithic culture of the ancient Baden region which spread over much of central Europe, and developed out of late Stone Age Lengyel culture. It is characterized by metal objects such as axe handles and plain, dark pottery. Images of domesticated horses are appear in artifacts as are four-wheeled carts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
